situational irony in tkam can anyone give me an example of situational irony in to kill a mockingbird omg we had that exact same question on my tkam unit in my english class a few examples tom robinson the guy scouts dad is trying to help dies in the end which seems completely opposite of what we think is going to happen we think that aticus is going to somehow save him because he is a good lawyer motty's house burns down and she doesnt seem upset i think it was that person anyways who's house burnt down situational irony is very easy to find just find something in the text which happens which seems completely opposite of what you thought was going to happen or what the book convinces you is going to happen To Kill a Mockingbird Irony Theory of conduct Kyle Broflovski Situationist John Kerr Fahrenheit 451 Scouting Pitaten Ironic (song) Eutheism, dystheism, and maltheism Grandview, U.S.A. History of the English Bible Social rule Kain (Legacy of Kain) PANICS Unified Modeling Language A Course In Miracles Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Postmodernism Lord of the Flies Situation comedy Humour Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix Deconstruction God Emperor of Dune Please Save My Earth Rain Man The Faerie Queene Appeal New Testament Darth Vader Internet phenomenon Communist Party of India (Marxist-Leninist) Janashakti Consensus decision-making Kitsch Boy Scouts of America Lolita Miss Saigon English grammar Theodicy Historical Jesus National Hockey League Dinosaur Comics Bad Wolf Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Joke Anatomy of Criticism Eminem Tom Coburn Force (Star Wars) Leo Wyatt Too Short a Season (TNG episode) Father's Day (Doctor Who) Battle of Jutland Grammatical mood Debugging Friends Transactional analysis Figure of speech Philosophical Investigations Antony and Cleopatra Tacitus About a Boy World Series The Three Musketeers Humphrey Bogart AFI 100 Years series Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Socrates Pretty Good Privacy The Lion, 